The paper deals with learning algorithms in repeated games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the convergence of these algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of shifting experts in dynamic population games, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of bandit feedback, which is a topic in statistics and probability (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of fast convergence, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY).
